        <h3>
            What happens in information technology management?
        </h3>
    </article>
    @* What happens in information technology management? *@
    <div>
        <p>
        <ul class="h5">
            <li>
                Determining business requirements for IT systems
            </li>
            <li>
                Managing IT budgets and costs
            </li>
            <li>
                Monitoring safety and compliance
            </li>
            <li>
                Controlling system and network security
            </li>
            <li>
                Implemented new software hardware and data systems
            </li>
            <li>
                Providing technical or help desk support
            </li>
        </ul>
        </p>
    </div>
    @* So what does all this do? *@
    <article>
        <h3>So, what does all this do?</h3>
        <p>
            Determines Information Technology strategies and goals for the business and ensure they are implemented.
        </p>

        <p>
            Processes, Software Hardware, and Systems using a business environment to conduct day-to-day operations.
        </p>
    </article>
    <h3>Advantages of Information technology management</h3>
    @* Advantages of Information technology management *@
    <article>
        <p>
        <ul class="h5">
            <li>
                There are very few business processes that do not depend on or cannot benefit from information
                technology.
            </li>
            <li>
                Information technology management allows businesses to manage their data efficiently regardless of
                its
                form.
            </li>
            <li>
                Information technology management allow employees to be more productive, but it can also be tailored
                to
                suit a company's specific needs.
            </li>
        </ul>
        </p>
    </article>
    @* paths of itm *@
    <div>
        <p>
            Information technology management have several career paths as it has best of both worlds that is
            business
            and
            information technology, and it requires strong analytical and mathematical problem-solving skills such
            as:
        <ol class="h5">
            <li>
                Project management
            </li>
            <li>
                Data security and role management
            </li>
            <li>
                Data organization and analysis
            </li>
            <li>
                System analysis design and organization
            </li>
            <li>
                Software and Hardware assessment
            </li>
        </ol>
        </p>
    </div>
